Famous photographer Bobby Pall recently held an art and book launch christened, Vanishing Songs of the Warrior. His art showcased powerful photographic images that depict African
culture and heritage in its truest form, which are cast in black and white
photography. In attendance were Education CS Amina Mohammed, Village Market chairman Manish Shah, Imaging Solutions MD Anish Harania, Mexican Ambassador Erasmo Martinez, Kenya's Ambassador to Tanzania Kazungu Kambi and Footprints Press publisher Susan Wakhungu.